et the job done. It was a challenging environment, but Tim led by example and quickly gained the respect of his colleagues and peers. \n\nTim made a huge impact in a short period, and I have no hesitation in working with him again. I wish him well with his future endeavours.", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Damian Ball", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "Group General Manager - at Cafe del Mar, Australasia", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/damian-ball-50635525/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAU2bZYBiJ-qPAbb8F6U-HmIHmf2RWSHYzI", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "Ankit reported directly to Tim", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "November 27, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "Its an honour to have this opputunity to write about Tim. \n\"A visionary, epitome of knowledge, skillful, zealous and caring. Tim did a fantastic job throughout at IBN battuta gate hotel and Oceana Beach club, from Pre-opening till it was established. Always a favourite of staffs, Tim is a people's person\".\nGiven oppurtunity, I would like to rejoin Tim to learn more from him.", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Ankit Sharan", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "Director of Food and Beverage | Passionate Hotelier", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ankitsharan/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAJqVK8BHBDM1PsbHlbHuDQQEtPUWypcssI", "recommendationsReceived/2/context": "Salvatore worked with Tim on the same team", "recommendationsReceived/2/date": "June 24, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/2/description": "It is with great pleasure that I write this Recommendation for Tim Tate as I have known Him on a personal and professional level for a number of years. In 2009 we both joined Movenpick Hotels and Resort where Tim's great Team work and Leadership shone brightly in all facets of Brand Standards, Restaurant Concepts and Food and Beverage Development. Tim’s greatest attribute is his calm and thoughtful personality making him a great leader to aspire to and absorb from. His interpersonal skills both at Management and Rank and file level are essential when trying to open 4 hotels and build business. He is of very strong character and always performs with dynamic approach and hunger for the betterment and delivery of service. I would have no hesitation in working with Tim again and wish him all the best in his new challenges to come.", "recommendationsReceived/2/name": "Salvatore Silvestrino", "recommendationsReceived/2/subtitle": "Executive Chef | Brand Ambassador | Pre-Opening Specialist | Food & Beverage Enthusiast | Culinary Visionary | Menu Development | Mentoring & Kitchen Operations | Strong Farm to Table Focus |", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/salvatoresilvestrino/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAANfpdEBOqDfN2o7EcdahrVPYt-TjRZH5Pw", "recommendationsReceived/3/context": "Dr. Craig managed Tim directly", "recommendationsReceived/3/date": "June 11, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/3/description": "To Whom it may concern:\n\nIt gives me great pleasure to write this recommendation for Tim.  I had the pleasure of working alongside Tim as we pioneered a new brand of hotels into the Dubai market.  Tim was a polished leader and a consummate professional as he led the Food & Beverage Department.  He was a key performer within the Executive team and I was impressed with his commitment, passion and drive for success.   \n\nTim & I worked hand in hand on many projects and he continually impressed me with his knowledge, and hunger to succeed.  He led his team diligently, and made sure that his commitment was echoed in them.\n\nHe interacted well with both his team and the Corporate Office and was selected for many high level projects because of his commitment to quality.     \n\nHe invested much time in both OS&E specification and setting up revolutionary standards from scratch and achieved great results.\n\nHe is a very strong performer and I would be happy to recommend him to any employer who is looking for a young, dynamic, hungry and driven hotelier who has his eyes only for the prize.\n\nHe is a pleasure to work with and I would be happy to speak on his behalf at any time.", "recommendationsReceived/3/name": "Dr. Craig Cook ", "recommendationsReceived/3/subtitle": "Chief Executive Officer, The Brain & Performance Centre, A DP World Company and Gulf Business Awards - Healthcare Leader of the Year 2025", "recommendationsReceived/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/craigcook01/", "recommendationsReceived/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAZTWVEBEpTorVWJphNaHvwLTN8wO2xblWY", "recommendationsReceived/4/context": "Tim was Sundeep's client", "recommendationsReceived/4/date": "April 12, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/4/description": "Tim was very methodical and practical in his approach. He was understanding and had extensive product and working knowledge in F&B thus helping us to source the products specified by him for Moevenpick Hotels. \n\nSundeep", "recommendationsReceived/4/name": "Sundeep Fernandes", "recommendationsReceived/4/subtitle": "Social media Director, Trainer Project management and Procurement, Humorous Content creator", "recommendationsReceived/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sundeep-fernandes-41542316/", "recommendationsReceived/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAANECJEBpA0ccrztihQckJzmzR0aXLUPkIA", "recommendationsReceived/5/context": "Robert reported directly to Tim", "recommendationsReceived/5/date": "March 20, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/5/description": "With his drive to be the best and attention to details, Tim was the driving force behind the opening of West 14th New York Prime @ the Oceana hotel and spa. His ability to motivate and to lead by example was instrumental in not only getting the restaurant open on time and on budget, but also laying the groundwork for it to become one of Dubai’s destination restaurants.  \n\nTim grasped not only the concept of West 14th, but also of the Oceana Beach Club, on which the restaurant is located. Managing this satellite location exerts demands above and beyond any normal operation, and Tim took those demands in stride. With his professional demeanor and willingness to do whatever is necessary, Tim has been an invaluable asset to the operation from pre-opening through the present operational mode.", "recommendationsReceived/5/name": "Robert Conaway", "recommendationsReceived/5/subtitle": "Entrepreneur (F&B / AI) | Executive Chef", "recommendationsReceived/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/robconaway/", "recommendationsReceived/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAAGzMIBI3PK92n016CXBLf2cNOYObdKmUU", "recommendationsReceived/6/context": "Andreas was senior to Tim but didn't manage Tim directly", "recommendationsReceived/6/date": "March 7, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/6/description": "Tim is a dedicated Hotel professional who invested considerabel time and effort to deliver an excellent product with limited resources. He is resourceful and will always find workable alternatives.", "recommendationsReceived/6/name": "Andreas Trauttmansdorff", "recommendationsReceived/6/subtitle": "Love my life", "recommendationsReceived/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/andreastrauttmansdorff/", "recommendationsReceived/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAEyitwB2vu8M-dYAc9T0ua0-hFHbECShTg", "recommendationsReceived/7/context": "Brenton reported directly to Tim", "recommendationsReceived/7/date": "March 7, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/7/description": "I worked with Tim for the past 18 months and found him to be a highly effective and competent professional in his field of expertise. \nHis personality is a key strength, making him an excellent role model and a person to whom others warm quickly, which is essential when trying to build business. Tim works tirelessly to give 100% commitment to whomever he is working with and spares no effort to meet and indeed exceed, his objectives. Tim will always bring value to whatever organisiation he is working for and I recommend him without hestiation. Tim supports his team giving 100% loyalty to his employees, company and owners.", "recommendationsReceived/7/name": "Brenton Coghlan", "recommendationsReceived/7/subtitle": "General Manager Hospitality at Exclusive", "recommendationsReceived/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/brentoncoghlan/", "recommendationsReceived/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAAtaNwBSYJsGU-5MX6lMPNVoD3kbTt8XEI", "recommendationsReceived/8/context": "Bryan M. worked with Tim on the same team", "recommendationsReceived/8/date": "March 1, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/8/description": "Tim is a sound professional with terrific Food & Beverage knowledge. He was very well respected by his peers and his work ethic was excellent. As a true specialist Tim was very honest, transparent, reliable, extremely hard working and developed his team around him to ensure complete success. I really enjoyed his contributions to the team, as his sincere and genuine approach was well received.", "recommendationsReceived/8/name": "Bryan M. Bourgeois", "recommendationsReceived/8/subtitle": "Vice President of Operations at Grand Living", "recommendationsReceived/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/bryan-m-bourgeois-31821b10/", "recommendationsReceived/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAIq9QQBru2M8-OVS92ytfwhU4qKBUZ_rug", "skills/0/title": "Food & Beverage", "skills/1/title": "Micros", "skills/2/title": "Pre-opening", "skills/3/title": "Resorts", "skills/4/title": "Hotel Management", "skills/5/title": "Hospitality Management", "skills/6/title": "Front Office", "skills/7/title": "Luxury", "skills/8/title": "Menu Development", "skills/9/title": "Hospitality", "skills/10/title": "Opera", "skills/11/title": "Tourism", "skills/12/title": "Hospitality Industry", "skills/13/title": "Banquets", "skills/14/title": "Hotels", "skills/15/title": "Training", "skills/16/tit